{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_136","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the ticket in [surface_wave_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_wave_execution.py#L193). The new library-owned API resolves operator assets plus Milestone 7 coupling bundles into a deterministic `ResolvedSurfaceWaveExecutionPlan`, exposes arm-plan entrypoints, and executes coupled multi-neuron wave steps through `CoupledSurfaceWaveCircuit` with realized coupling metadata captured in run outputs. The presynaptic patch-cloud sampling, signed/delayed postsynaptic injection, deterministic topology handling, and clear failure paths for missing assets, incompatible anchors, and unusable delays are in [surface_wave_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_wave_execution.py#L299), [surface_wave_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_wave_execution.py#L742), and [surface_wave_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_wave_execution.py#L1000).\n\nAdded regression coverage in [test_surface_wave_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_surface_wave_execution.py#L47) for deterministic delayed propagation, deterministic shuffled-topology permutation behavior, and explicit failure cases for bad delay and anchor metadata. I also fixed the coupling-plan hash path so NumPy-backed values are normalized before hashing, which keeps realized coupling metadata deterministic [surface_wave_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_wave_execution.py#L1108) [surface_wave_execution.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_wave_execution.py#L1408).\n\nVerified with `.venv/bin/python -m unittest tests.test_surface_wave_execution` and `make test` (`123` tests passed). I could not stage or create the requested commit here because `.git` is mounted read-only in this sandbox, and `git add` fails with `Unable to create '.git/index.lock': Read-only file system`. Unrelated dirty files in the worktree were left untouched."}}
